</div>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="64" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:48.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Number of Years of Credited Service as of May&nbsp;31,
2005, the date the plan was frozen.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Amounts shown in this column are calculated as of May&nbsp;31,
2007, which is the measurement date for reporting purposes in the Company&#146;s
Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K for Fiscal 2007. See footnote 6 to the Consolidated
Financial Statements contained in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K
for an explanation of the assumptions made by the Company in determining the
amounts reported in this column. </font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 11.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Clark and Mr.&nbsp;McDonald are
not participants in the defined benefit portion of the SKERP.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 1.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SKERP&nbsp;&#151; Defined Benefit Portion<a name="SkerpDefinedBenefitPortion_235853"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company provides
supplemental retirement benefits to certain executives and key employees under
the SKERP. The SKERP, which is a non-qualified plan, contains a defined benefit
portion and a defined contribution portion (discussed below). Only Mr.&nbsp;Storch,
Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko and Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer participate in the defined benefit
portion of the SKERP, the material terms and conditions of which include the
following:</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Benefit Accruals:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Under
the defined benefit portion of the SKERP, benefits were accrued until October&nbsp;1,
2001 pursuant to a formula that provides a monthly single life annuity at
retirement at age 65 equal to (i)&nbsp;<font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font face="Symbol">&#164;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;">12</font> of 60% (50%
for Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko and Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer) of Final Average Earnings less (ii)&nbsp;the
monthly benefit payable under the Company&#146;s Retirement Plan determined as of October&nbsp;1,
2001. For purposes of this benefit formula, (i)&nbsp;Final Average Earnings is
defined as <font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font face="Symbol">&#164;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;">5</font>
of a participant&#146;s Compensation during the consecutive five years within the
last 10 years preceding termination of employment during which such
Compensation was the highest, and (ii)&nbsp;Compensation is defined as the
participant&#146;s income reported on Form&nbsp;W-2, including pre-tax
contributions to the Retirement Savings Plan, reduced by the income
attributable to restricted stock and stock options, reimbursements or other
expense allowances and fringe benefits. Benefits
accrued on and after October&nbsp;1, 2001 under the defined benefit portion of
the SKERP will accrue pursuant to a formula that provides a monthly single life
annuity at retirement at age 65 equal to <font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font face="Symbol">&#164;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;">12</font> of 60% (50% for Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko and
Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer) of 25% of the percentage increase in the participant&#146;s base
salary from September&nbsp;30, 2001 to the date of the participant&#146;s
termination of employment. The benefits accrued by each of the three
participants under this formula as of May&nbsp;31, 2006 have been or will be transferred to the defined contribution
portion of the SKERP and held in an account established and maintained
thereunder for each participant, so that as of June&nbsp;1, 2008 the entire
benefit accrued as of </p>


 <p style="line-height:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">32</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='32',FILE='C:\fc\22918275233_H11179_2359682\19818-1-ee.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 17 18:27 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">May&nbsp;31,
2006 will have been transferred. Of the amounts shown in the &#147;Present Value of
Accumulated Benefit&#148; column above, the following amounts remain to be
transferred to the defined contribution portion of the SKERP: Mr.&nbsp;Storch
$586,000; Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko $93,300; Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer $310,300.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Benefits accrued under the
defined benefit portion of the SKERP for all other participants, including the
other named executive officers, ceased on October&nbsp;1, 2001 and were
distributed to them in a lump sum as soon as practicable thereafter.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Benefit Entitlement:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>A
participant is eligible to receive the benefit accrued under the SKERP
following termination of employment when he attains age 65. If a participant
terminates employment after he has attained age 55 and his age plus years of
service equal or exceed 62, benefits will be paid on the date of his
termination or on a date no later than 15 years after termination of
employment, as previously specified by the participant.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Form&nbsp;of Benefit Payment:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Each
participant has previously elected to have the remainder of his retirement
benefit paid in a lump sum. The assumptions set forth in the Company&#146;s
Retirement Plan will be used to convert the retirement benefits from an annuity
payment to a lump sum. The participant may change the time or form of payment
in accordance with procedures set forth in the SKERP.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 11.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Forfeiture Events:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>A
participant will forfeit the retirement benefit if his employment is terminated
due to theft, embezzlement or fraud or willful misconduct in the performance of
his duties that materially injures the Company, or if during employment or the
one-year period thereafter the participant violates the covenant not to compete
contained in the SKERP. As a condition to receiving his retirement benefit, a
participant must agree in writing to return his benefit, plus 8% interest, in
the event of such a forfeiture. The forfeiture provision does not apply if the
participant&#146;s termination of employment causes benefits to be paid to him under
Change in Control provisions of any agreement between the participant and the
Company.</p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 1.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Retirement Plan<a name="RetirementPlan_000107"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company&#146;s Retirement Plan
is a tax-qualified pension plan. Benefit accruals ceased under the Retirement
Plan with respect to most participants, including the named executive officers,
effective June&nbsp;1, 2005. The material terms and conditions of the
Retirement Plan as they pertain to the named executive officers are as follows:</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Benefit formula:</font></i></font><i><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-style:italic;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></i>Until January&nbsp;1, 2000 benefits were
accrued pursuant to a formula that provides a monthly single life annuity at
retirement at age 65 equal to 1-<font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font face="Symbol">&#164;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;">2</font>%
of the participant&#146;s Final Average Earnings reduced by the participant&#146;s Social
Security offset determined under the Plan, multiplied by the participant&#146;s
years of Credited Service (up to 20). Effective as of January&nbsp;1, 2000, the
Plan was converted to a cash balance type of plan subject to a &#147;grandfather&#148;
provision applicable to certain participants based on age and years of service.
An account is maintained for each participant which consists of (i)&nbsp;an
opening account balance equal to the then present value of the benefit accrued
by the participant under the prior formula as of December&nbsp;31, 1999, (ii)&nbsp;quarterly
contributions made by the Company equal to a percentage of compensation based
on the participant&#146;s age and years of Credited Service, and (iii)&nbsp;quarterly
interest credits made by the Company equal to 25% of the 30-year Treasury
securities interest rate for the second month preceding the beginning of each
quarter. For purposes of the benefit formulae, &#147;Final Average Earnings&#148; and &#147;Compensation&#148;
have the same definitions as used in the SKERP, as discussed above.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The benefits under the
Retirement Plan generally ceased accruing on June&nbsp;1, 2005, although the
participants&#146; cash balance accounts continue to be credited with interest until
the benefits are distributed. In connection with the benefit cessation, the
Company will continue to make transition credits to the accounts of certain
non-highly compensated participants until they have attained 20 years of
Credited Service. None of the named executive officers are eligible for these
transition credits.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 5.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Vesting:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Participants
are eligible to receive benefits from the Retirement Plan after completing five
years of Vesting Service.</p>


 <p style="line-height:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">33</font></p>
</div><br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='33',FILE='C:\fc\22918275233_H11179_2359682\19818-1-ee.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 17 18:27 2007' -->



<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div>


<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Payment of Retirement Benefits:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Participants
can elect to receive their benefits upon termination of employment or they can
defer receipt of benefits until normal retirement age (age 65). A participant
who terminates employment after age 55 with 10 years of service can elect to
receive benefits early, with the normal retirement benefit being reduced by .5%
for each of the first 60 months by which the benefit commences before age 65
and .25% for each of the next 60 months by which the benefit commences before
age 65. A participant who is not eligible for a normal or early retirement but
who has 10 years of service can elect benefits at any time after attaining age
55, with the benefit reduced as described above. Any vested participant can
elect benefits at any time after termination of employment, with the benefit
actuarially reduced to reflect payment prior to age 65. The Retirement Plan
also provides for a disability retirement benefit.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Forms of Benefit Payment:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>The
normal form of benefit payment for a married participant is a joint and 50%
survivor annuity, and the normal form of benefit payment for an unmarried
participant is a single life annuity. Participants, with spousal consent if
applicable, can waive the normal form and elect to have benefits paid in
various annuity forms, which are the actuarial equivalent of the normal form,
or in a lump sum.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Retirement Savings Plan:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>In
connection with ceasing benefits under the Retirement Plan, the Company amended
its Retirement Savings Plan to provide additional benefits, as described below
in the discussion following the Nonqualified Compensation table.</p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Nonqualified Deferred
Compensation<a name="NonqualifiedDeferredCompensation_000144"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company provides non-qualified
deferred compensation benefits under the defined contribution portion of the
SKERP. The table below shows the contributions made by each named executive
officer and the Company in Fiscal 2007, the earnings accrued on the named
executive officer&#146;s account balance in Fiscal 2007 and the account balance at
May&nbsp;31, 2007.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Non-Qualified Deferred
Compensation Table <a name="NonqualifiedDeferredCompensationT_234631"></a></font></b></p>

</div>

<div style="line-height:9.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="64" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:48.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">The amount of contributions made by each named
executive officer and reported in this column in respect of salary deferrals in
Fiscal 2007 is included in each named executive officer&#146;s compensation reported
on the Summary Compensation Table as Salary. The amount of contributions reported
in this column also reflects deferral of cash bonuses paid in Fiscal 2007 but
earned and reported on the Summary Compensation Table for Fiscal 2006.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">This amount includes the amounts transferred from the defined
benefit portion of the SKERP to the defined contribution portion of the SKERP during
fiscal 2007 for benefits earned prior to fiscal 2007, in the following
amounts:&#160; Mr.&nbsp;Storch, $567,900; Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko,
$90,400; and Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer, $299,500. These amounts are not included in the
All Other Compensation Table.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">The investment earnings reported in this column for
each named executive officer are not reported on the Summary Compensation
Table.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">The aggregate balance as of May&nbsp;31,
2007 reported in this column for each named executive officer reflects amounts
that have been previously reported as compensation on the Summary Compensation
Table for Fiscal 2007 or prior years, except the following amounts of earnings
included in the account balance:&#160; Mr.&nbsp;Storch,
$852,600; Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko, $138,500; Mr.&nbsp;Clark, $8,800,
Mr.&nbsp;McDonald, $123,100 and Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer, $398,000, and the following
cumulative amounts transferred from the defined benefit portion of the SKERP:
Mr.&nbsp;Storch, $1,126,800; Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko, $179,500; and, Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer,
$593,700.</font></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">34</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='34',FILE='C:\fc\229182830221_H11179_2359682\19818-1-eg.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 17 18:29 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SKERP&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;Defined
Contribution Portion<a name="SkerpAutotextEmdashMergeformatdef_234632"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The defined contribution portion of the SKERP covers
certain executives and key employees, including all of the named executive
officers, and provides the portion of a participant&#146;s benefit that cannot be
paid under the Retirement Savings Plan due to any Internal Revenue Code limits,
including the limit on the amount of compensation that can be taken into
account in determining benefits ($220,000, in 2006 and $225,000 in 2007). The
material terms and conditions include the following:</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Contributions:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Each
participant may make an election prior to the beginning of a calendar year to
contribute a portion of his base salary (up to 75%) for that calendar year that
exceeds the Code&#146;s compensation limit and a portion of the bonus (up to 75%)
paid to him for the Company&#146;s fiscal year beginning in such calendar year that
exceeds the Code&#146;s compensation limit. The Company makes a matching
contribution under the SKERP using the formula in the Savings Plan (i.e., 20%
of the participant&#146;s salary and bonus deferrals made under the SKERP, up to 5%
of such salary and bonus), as well as the portion of the Company&#146;s profit
sharing contribution that could not be made under the Savings Plan due to the
Code&#146;s compensation limit. Beginning January&nbsp;1, 2006, the Company also makes
annual supplemental contributions to the accounts of the Chief Executive
Officer (22% of base salary), and certain other executive officers (10% of base
salary). &#160;To receive a credit of this
contribution, the eligible participant must be employed as of the day before
the contribution is made to the SKERP (unless termination of employment is due
to death or disability).</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Storch, Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko and Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer
also have amounts held in a supplemental account that were or will be
transferred from the defined benefit portion of the SKERP, which represent the
lump sum value of each participant&#146;s accrued benefit as of May&nbsp;31, 2006
under the defined benefit portion. Once transferred, such amounts are subject
to the term and conditions of the defined contribution portion of the SKERP.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Vesting:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>A
participant is fully vested in amounts attributable to his own deferral
contributions, as well as the Company matching and profit sharing contributions.
A participant vests in amounts attributable to Company supplemental
contributions upon the earlier of age 57 with 15 years of service, or age 65.
Mr.&nbsp;Storch, Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko and Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer are fully vested in
the amounts of their benefits transferred from the defined benefit portion of
the SKERP.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Investments:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Each
participant&#146;s plan accounts are credited with earnings and losses based on
investment alternatives made available by the plan committee and selected by
the participant from time to time. The investment options currently offered
under the SKERP consist of 24 mutual funds including 10 &#147;Life Cycle&#148; fund
choices. Participants may change investment elections at any time.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Distributions:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Distribution
of a participant&#146;s accounts is generally made upon the participant&#146;s
termination of employment or on a date no later than 15 years after termination
of employment, as previously specified by the participant. Participants were to
elect by December&nbsp;31, 2005 whether their accounts are to be paid in a lump
sum or installments not to exceed 15 years (a participant who failed to make an
election will have his account paid in a lump sum). Notwithstanding the
foregoing, (i)&nbsp;a participant may elect distribution of the portion of his
accounts earned and vested as of December&nbsp;31, 2004 (and earnings thereon)
upon six month&#146;s advance written election or if such distribution is subject to
a 10% forfeiture; (ii)&nbsp;a participant can change the time and form of payment
of the portion of his accounts earned and vested after December&nbsp;31, 2004
in accordance with procedures set forth in the plan; (iii)&nbsp;a participant
can elect a distribution at any time in order to satisfy an unforeseeable
hardship (as defined in the plan); (iv)&nbsp;in the event of a potential Change
in Control of the Company (as determined by the Board), the portion of the
participant&#146;s accounts earned and vested as of December&nbsp;31, 2004
(including earnings thereon) will be distributed in an immediate lump sum; and (v)&nbsp;in
the event of adverse financial condition of the Company occurring prior to January&nbsp;1,
2008 (as specified in the plan), the Company can elect to distribute within 30
days the amounts credited to participant&#146;s accounts as of March&nbsp;21, 2006
in an immediate lump sum. Distributions to &#147;key </p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">35</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='35',FILE='C:\fc\229182830221_H11179_2359682\19818-1-eg.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 17 18:29 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">employees&#148; as defined in Code Section&nbsp;409A upon
termination of employment will not be paid earlier than six months following
such termination.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Forfeiture Events:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>A
participant will forfeit the portion of his plan accounts attributable to
Company supplemental contributions and to amounts transferred from the defined
benefit portion of the SKERP, if applicable, if his employment is terminated
due to theft, embezzlement or fraud or willful misconduct in the performance of
his duties that materially injures the Company, or if during employment or the
one-year period thereafter the participant violates the covenant not to compete
contained in the SKERP. As a condition to receiving such amounts, a participant
must agree in writing to return such amounts, plus 8% interest, in the event of
such a forfeiture. The forfeiture provision does not apply if the participant&#146;s
termination of employment causes benefits to be paid to him under Change in
Control provisions of any agreement between the participant and the Company.</p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Retirement Savings Plan<a name="RetirementSavingsPlan_234632"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Retirement Savings Plan is a tax-qualified
retirement plan that covers all U.S. employees generally (excluding certain
union employees), including the named executive officers. The material terms
and conditions are as follows:</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Contributions:</font></i></font><i><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-style:italic;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></i>A participant can elect to defer 1% to 75% of
his Compensation on a pre-tax basis, up to a maximum of $15,500 for 2007, or
$20,500 if age 50 or older. Participation for non-union employees is automatic,
at a 3% deferral rate, unless the participant affirmatively elects not to
participate or to participate with a different deferral amount. The Company
provides a matching contribution, a profit sharing contribution and a
retirement benefit contribution. The current matching contribution is made as
of each payroll period in an amount equal to 20% of the participant&#146;s pre-tax
contributions (up to 5% of compensation) to the Plan for such payroll period. The
profit sharing contribution is made as of the end of each calendar year and is
based on the participant&#146;s pre-tax contributions and the economic performance
of the participant&#146;s operating unit and is equal to a percentage of the
participant&#146;s compensation, up to 4%. The retirement benefit contribution,
which is also made as of the end of each calendar year, was added to the Plan,
effective June&nbsp;1, 2005, and is equal to a percentage of compensation (up
to 4%) based on the participant&#146;s age and years of credited service. A
participant must have earned a year of service to be eligible for a retirement
benefit contribution, and generally must be employed on the last day of the
calendar year to receive a profit sharing contribution. Compensation for
purposes of determining contributions includes cash compensation shown as
income on the participant&#146;s Form&nbsp;W-2, reduced by pre-tax
contributions to the plan and excluding the income attributable to restricted
stock options, reimbursements or other expense allowances and fringe benefits
and subject to the Code&#146;s compensation limit ($225,000 for 2007).</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Investments:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Each
participant&#146;s plan accounts are credited with earnings and losses based on
investment alternatives made available by the plan committee and selected by
the participant from time to time. The investment options currently offered
under the plan consist of 24<b>  </b>mutual funds
including 10 &#147;Life Cycle&#148; fund choices. Participants may change investment
elections at any time.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Vesting:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Participants
hired prior to July&nbsp;1, 1999 are fully vested in their accounts under the
plan. Participants hired on or after January&nbsp;1, 1999 are fully vested in
their pre-tax contribution accounts, and vest in the Company contribution
accounts at a rate equal to 33<font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font face="Symbol">&#164;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.0pt;">3</font>% for each year of vesting service
(subject to full vesting upon age 65, death or disability.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Distributions:</font></i></font><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>Participants
can elect distributions of the plan accounts upon termination of employment, in
a lump sum, an eligible rollover distribution, or, if early or normal
retirement has been attained, in installments not to exceed 15 years.</p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">36</font></p>

<div>


<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;">Potential
Payments Upon Termination or Change in Control of the Company<a name="PotentialPaymentsUponTerminationO_234633"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
Company provides certain benefits to eligible employees upon certain types of
termination of employment, including a termination of employment following a
Change in Control of the Company. These benefits are in addition to the
benefits to which the employees would be entitled upon a termination of
employment generally (i.e., vested retirement benefits accrued as of the date
of termination, stock options and restricted stock that are otherwise vested as
of the date of termination and the right to elect continued health coverage
pursuant to COBRA). These benefits as they pertain to the named executive
officers are as described and set forth in the tables below.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Employment Agreement of
David P. Storch<a name="EmploymentAgreementOfDavidP_Storc_234633"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company has entered into an
employment agreement with Mr.&nbsp;Storch with a term that ends on May&nbsp;31,
2010 unless the parties mutually agree to an extension. The agreement provides
the following severance benefits:</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Termination
&#151; Prior </font><font style="font-style:italic;"><i>to a Change in Control:</i></font></font></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; If employment agreement term expires without extension and Mr.&nbsp;Storch&#146;s
employment subsequently terminates for reasons other than Cause, or if prior to
a Change in Control either the Company terminates his employment without Cause
or Mr.&nbsp;Storch terminates his employment for Good Reason,&#160; he is entitled to (i)&nbsp;continued payment
of his base salary for 36 months, and (ii)&nbsp;a lump sum payment equal to
three times the average of the cash incentive bonus paid to him for the
preceding three fiscal years of the Company. If Mr.&nbsp;Storch&#146;s termination
is due to retirement after age 55, he and his eligible dependents are entitled
to continued coverage under the Company&#146;s medical, dental and executive health
programs for his lifetime (or until he obtains health coverage from a new
employer). Payments cease upon any material breach of the confidentiality and
non-compete provisions set forth in the agreement, which are in effect for the
two-year period following any voluntary termination of employment or a
termination of employment by the Company without Cause prior to a Change in
Control.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Termination </font><font style="font-style:italic;"><i>&#151; Following a Change in Control:</i></font></font></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; If Mr.&nbsp;Storch&#146;s employment is
terminated within 24&nbsp;months following a Change in Control either by the
Company for other than Cause or disability or by Mr.&nbsp;Storch for Good
Reason, or if his employment terminates for any reason other than disability or
death during the 30-day period following the 24th month after a Change in
Control, he is entitled to (i)&nbsp;an immediate lump sum payment equal to the
sum of (A)&nbsp;any unpaid salary and bonus earned for the preceding fiscal
year, (B)&nbsp;a prorata portion of the bonus that would have been paid to the
executive had he remained employed until the end of the fiscal year and all
performance targets were met, and (C)&nbsp;three times his base salary and cash
bonus for either the most recently completed fiscal year prior to the termination
or the preceding fiscal year, whichever produces the higher amount, (ii)&nbsp;continued
coverage for the executive and his dependents under the Company&#146;s welfare and
fringe benefit plans for three years following termination of employment (the
executive and his dependents can elect continued medical and dental coverage
pursuant to COBRA at the end of such three year period, (iii)&nbsp;a lump sum
payment of the additional benefits that would be earned under the Company&#146;s
Retirement Savings Plan and SKERP equal to the amount attributable to Company
contributions that would have been made had his elective contributions
continued and had he accumulated three additional years of service, and a
gross-up payment to cover any related income tax liability, (iv)&nbsp;Company-paid
outplacement services for the earlier of 18 months or the attainment of new
employment (up to a maximum Company expense of 3.5% of the amount paid to Mr.&nbsp;Storch
pursuant to (i)(C) above), (v)&nbsp;reasonable legal fees incurred by the
executive in enforcing the agreement, and (vi)&nbsp;a gross-up payment to cover
any excise and related tax liability arising under Section&nbsp;280G of the
Internal Revenue Code as a result of any payment or benefit arising under the
agreement. The agreement&#146;s non-compete provisions do not apply in the case of a
termination of employment following a Change in Control.</p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">37</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='37',FILE='C:\fc\234112935851_D11265_2368140\19818-1-ei.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:30 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Termination
</font><font style="font-style:italic;"><i>&#151; Disability:</i></font></font></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; If Mr.&nbsp;Storch&#146;s employment terminates
due to disability, Mr.&nbsp;Storch will receive payment pursuant to the Company&#146;s
disability plans then in effect and will continue to receive coverage under the
Company&#146;s medical, dental and life insurance plans for three years following
such termination.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The agreement also provides that
upon any Change in Control, all outstanding stock options and restricted stock
vest immediately, and all performance based restricted stock shares will be
awarded according to the performance matrix set forth in the&#160; agreement based on the higher of the target
or actual Company performance through the date of the Change in Control.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For purposes of the agreement:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;Change in Control&#148; means (i)&nbsp;a
person&#146;s acquisition of more than 35% of the voting power of the Company&#146;s
outstanding stock, (ii)&nbsp;a merger or consolidation of the Company that
results in the holders of the voting stock immediately prior thereto holding
less than 60% of the voting stock of the resulting or surviving entity, (iii)&nbsp;a
sale of substantially all of the Company&#146;s assets other than to an entity at
least 80% owned by the Company, or (iv)&nbsp;the election, without the consent
of the incumbent Board, of a majority of the directors then in office.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;Cause&#148; means Mr.&nbsp;Storch&#146;s (i)&nbsp;dishonesty,
intentional breach of fiduciary duty, or intentional wrongdoing, (ii)&nbsp;disregard
of proper direction from the Board or Company, or (iii)&nbsp;material breach of
the Agreement that is not cured within 30 days of receipt of notice from the
Company.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;Good Reason&#148;
means (i)&nbsp;a material reduction in the nature or scope of Mr.&nbsp;Storch&#146;s
duties or responsibilities or in his compensation (including benefits), (ii)&nbsp;his
determination that as a result of a material change in employment circumstances
he is unable to adequately carry out his duties, (iii)&nbsp;a material breach
of the Agreement by the Company that is not cured within 30 days of receipt of
notice from Mr.&nbsp;Storch, or (iv)&nbsp;a relocation of his primary place of
employment of 50 or more miles.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Severance
and Change in Control Agreements<a name="SeveranceAndChangeInControlAgreem_235156"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company has entered into severance
and change in control agreements with the named executive officers other than Mr.&nbsp;Storch
and with certain other key employees. The Agreements as they pertain to these
named executive officers provide for the following benefits upon the following
types of employment termination:</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Termination
</font><font style="font-style:italic;"><i>&#151; Prior
to a Change in Control:</i></font></font></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; If a Change in Control of the Company has not occurred and the
executive&#146;s employment is terminated by the Company for other than Cause, he is
entitled to (i)&nbsp;continued salary for 12 months, or if earlier, until the
executive obtains comparable employment, (ii)&nbsp;any earned bonus not yet
paid for the preceding fiscal year, and (iii)&nbsp;a prorata portion of the
bonus that would have been paid to the executive had he remained employed until
the end of the fiscal year in which the termination occurs. Any bonus will be
paid in a lump sum on the later of the time bonuses are paid to other officers
and the end of the severance period (with interest at the prime rate plus 1%
from the earlier of such dates). If the executive terminates his employment, or
if the Company terminates the executive&#146;s employment for Cause, the Company
may, but is not required to, pay the above-described severance benefits. Severance
payments will cease if the executive breaches the confidentiality or
non-compete provisions in the agreement, which are in effect for the one-year
severance period.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Termination
</font><font style="font-style:italic;"><i>&#151; Following
a Change in Control:</i></font></font></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; If
the executive&#146;s employment is terminated within 18 months (24 for Mr.&nbsp;Clark)
following a Change in Control by the Company for other than Cause or disability
or by the executive for Good Reason, or if the executive&#146;s employment
terminates for any reason other than disability or death during the 30-day
period following the 18<font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">th</font>&#160;month (24<font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">th</font>&#160;month for Mr.&nbsp;Clark)
after a Change in Control, he is entitled to (i)&nbsp;an immediate lump sum
payment equal to the sum of (A)&nbsp;any unpaid salary and bonus earned for the
preceding fiscal year, (B)&nbsp;a prorata portion of the bonus that would have
been paid to the executive had he remained employed until the end of the </p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">38</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='38',FILE='C:\fc\234112935851_D11265_2368140\19818-1-ei.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:30 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">fiscal year and all performance
targets were met (including the value of any restricted stock granted in lieu of
bonus), and (C)&nbsp;three times his base salary and cash bonus for either the
most recently completed fiscal year prior to the termination or the preceding
fiscal year, whichever produces the higher amount, (ii)&nbsp;continued coverage
for the executive and his dependents under the Company&#146;s welfare and fringe
benefit plans (medical, dental and life insurance plans for Mr.&nbsp;Clark) for
three years following termination of employment (the executive and his
dependents can elect continued medical and dental coverage pursuant to COBRA at
the end of such three year period), (iii)&nbsp;an immediate lump sum payment
equal to the actuarial equivalent of the additional benefits that would be
earned under the Company&#146;s retirement plans with three additional years of
service and for Mr.&nbsp;Romenesko, Mr.&nbsp;McDonald and Mr.&nbsp;Pulsifer, a
gross-up payment to cover any related income tax liability, (iv)&nbsp;Company-paid
outplacement services for the earlier of 18 months or the attainment of new
employment (up to a maximum Company expense of 3.5% of the amount paid to the
executive pursuant to (i)(C)&nbsp;above), (v)&nbsp;reasonable legal fees
incurred by the executive in enforcing the agreement, and (vi)&nbsp;a gross-up
payment to cover any excise and related tax liability arising under Section&nbsp;280G
of the Internal Revenue Code as a result of any payment or benefit arising
under the agreement. The agreements&#146; non-compete provisions do not apply in the
case of a termination of employment following a Change in Control.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Termination
</font><font style="font-style:italic;"><i>&#151; Disability:</i></font></font></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; If the executive&#146;s employment terminates
due to disability, the executive will receive payment pursuant to the Company&#146;s
disability plans then in effect and will continue to receive coverage under the
Company&#146;s medical, dental and life insurance plans for three years following
such termination.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;">The agreeme</font>nts also provide that upon any Change in Control,
all outstanding stock options and restricted stock will vest immediately.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For purposes of the agreements:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;Change in Control&#148; means (i)&nbsp;a
person&#146;s acquisition of more than 20% of the voting power of the Company&#146;s
outstanding stock, (ii)&nbsp;a merger or consolidation of the Company that
results in the holders of the voting stock immediately prior thereto holding
less than 60% of the voting stock of the resulting or surviving entity, (iii)&nbsp;a
sale of substantially all of the Company&#146;s assets other than to an entity at
least 80% owned by the Company, or (iv)&nbsp;the election, without the consent
of the incumbent Board, of the lesser of three directors or a majority of the
directors then in office.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;Cause&#148; means the executive&#146;s (i)&nbsp;dishonesty,
intentional breach of fiduciary duty, or intentional wrongdoing, (ii)&nbsp;disregard
of proper direction from the Board or Company, or (iii)&nbsp;material breach of
the Agreement that is not cured within 10 days of receipt of notice from the
Company.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;Good
Reason&#148; means (i)&nbsp;a material reduction in the nature or scope of the
executive&#146;s duties or responsibilities, or in his compensation (including
benefits), (ii)&nbsp;if Mr.&nbsp;Storch is not the Chief Executive Officer at
the time of termination, the executive&#146;s determination that as a result of a
material change in employment circumstances he is unable to adequately carry
out his duties, or (iii)&nbsp;a relocation of the executive&#146;s primary place of
employment by more than 100 miles.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Split
Dollar Insurance Agreements<a name="SplitDollarInsuranceAgreements_235454"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
Company has also entered into split dollar life insurance agreements with
certain key employees, including four of the named executive officers. Under
the agreements, the employees own the policies, except that the Company owns
the cash value portion of the policies. The Company funds the annual insurance
premiums for the policies during the term of the agreement subject to
reimbursement from the cash value or death benefit proceeds of the policies. Upon
a Change in Control of the Company (as defined above), the Company will prepay
all premiums, plus any amounts necessary for the cash value and death benefits
to be at the same level at the Change in Control date. If the executive&#146;s
employment terminates after a Change in Control and benefits are paid under the
</font></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">39</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='39',FILE='C:\fc\234112935851_D11265_2368140\19818-1-ei.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:30 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Severance
and Change in Control Agreements, the Split Dollar Agreements will continue for
the severance period.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Restricted
Stock and Stock Options<a name="RestrictedStockAndStockOptions_235516"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The severance and change in control
agreements provide that on a Change in Control of the Company, all restricted
stock and stock options immediately vest.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Storch&#146;s employment agreement
provides that on a Change in Control of the Company, all restricted stock and
stock options immediately vest, and all performance-restricted stock shares
will be awarded according to the performance matrix set forth in the agreement
based on the higher of the target or actual Company performance through the
Change in Control date.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A named executive officer&#146;s
termination of employment can also result in enhanced benefits under the
Company Stock Benefit Plan, depending on the reason for such termination:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">If the termination is due to
Retirement (as defined in the Plan), options continue to remain exercisable as
if employment continues. If the termination is due to Disability (as defined in
the Plan) or death, or if the Executive dies within three months of termination
for reasons other than cause, options will expire on the earlier of one year
from death or the expiration of the option by its terms.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">If the
termination is due to Retirement (as defined in the Plan) all restricted stock
awards vest as of such termination for awards having a grant date earlier than September&nbsp;1,
2004; awards having a grant date on or after 9/1/04 continue to vest in
accordance with their vesting schedule. If the termination is due to Disability
(as defined in the Plan) or death on or before the third anniversary of the
date of grant, then the difference between one-half of the total award shares
and the number of shares already vested will vest as of such termination. If
the termination is due to Disability or death after the third anniversary of
the date of grant, all awards shares will vest as of such termination.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Table of Potential Payments<br>
Upon Termination of Employment<br>
or Change in Control</font></b></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;text-indent:0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:normal;">The tables set forth below quantify the additional benefits
described above that would be paid to each named executive officer under the
following termination or change in control event, assuming a change in control or
a termination occurred on June&nbsp;1, 2007.</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;font-weight:normal;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="64" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:48.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Mr.&nbsp;McDonald
is excluded from the tables because he is no longer an employee of the Company.</p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">40</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Under the Stock Benefit Plan, all restricted stock
vests upon a Change in Control of the Company. This amount reflects the number
of shares that would have vested upon a Change in Control on June&nbsp;1, 2007,
based on the number of shares multiplied by $32.50, the closing price of the
common stock on May&nbsp;31, 2007. All stock options are already vested.</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="64" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:48.0pt;"></div>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">Per employment agreement (Mr.&nbsp;Storch) and severance
and change in control agreements.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">Per employment agreement (Mr.&nbsp;Storch) and severance
and change in control agreements.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">If termination is due to retirement, options remain
exercisable for their term. This amount reflects the value of the options
remaining exercisable past the 90 day post-termination period that would
otherwise apply upon termination without Cause on June&nbsp;1, 2007.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">If termination is due to retirement, restricted stock
awards continue to vest in accordance with the award&#146;s vesting schedule subject
to compliance with non-compete covenants applicable to all awards.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">5</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">Available if Mr.&nbsp;Storch retires after age 55.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">6</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">Per employment agreement (Mr.&nbsp;Storch) and severance
and change in control agreements.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">7</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">Under the Stock Benefit Plan, if termination is due to
death or disability, options remain exercisable for one year, or if earlier,
until the options expire by their terms. This amount reflects the value of the
options remaining exercisable past the 90 day post-termination period that
would otherwise apply upon termination without Cause.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:4.5pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">8</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;">This amount reflects the value of the restricted stock
that would have vested upon termination due to death or disability at June&nbsp;1,
2007, based on the number of shares, multiplied by $32.50, the closing price of
the stock on May&nbsp;31, 2007.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Termination
Following Change in Control</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><a name="TerminationFollowingChangeInContr_235940"></a></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Per employment agreement (Mr.&nbsp;Storch) and severance
and change in control agreements.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Vesting
of restricted stock occurs upon the Change in Control. See Table captioned
&#147;Change in Control (No termination of Employment)&#148; table.</font></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">41</font></p>
</div><br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='41',FILE='C:\fc\23411311472_D11265_2368140\19818-1-ek.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:32 2007' -->



<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div>


<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;">VIII. REPORT OF AUDIT COMMITTEE<a name="Viii_ReportOfAuditCommittee_000716"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During Fiscal 2007, the Audit
Committee was comprised of five independent directors. Each member of the Audit
Committee is independent within the meaning of the applicable SEC regulations,
NYSE rules&nbsp;and the Company&#146;s Categorical Standards and Policy for
Determining Director Independence, and is qualified as an &#147;audit committee
financial expert.&#148;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company&#146;s management is
primarily responsible for the Company&#146;s financial statements and the quality
and integrity of the reporting process and systems of internal control. The
Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm is responsible for
auditing the Company&#146;s financial statements and management&#146;s assessment and the
effectiveness of internal controls over financial reporting and for expressing
opinions thereon. The Audit Committee has the authority to obtain advice and
assistance from outside legal, accounting or other advisors as the Audit
Committee deems necessary to carry out its duties with funding from the Company.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In fulfilling its oversight
responsibilities, the Audit Committee has reviewed and discussed the Company&#146;s
audited financial statements for the fiscal year ended May&nbsp;31, 2007, with
the Company&#146;s management and representatives of the Company&#146;s independent
registered public accounting firm, including a discussion of the reasonableness
of significant judgments and accounting estimates, and clarity of disclosures
in the financial statements. The Audit Committee also reviewed with management
and the independent registered public accounting firm the preparation of the
financial statements and related disclosures contained in the Company&#146;s
earnings announcements and quarterly reports. Management has represented to the
Audit Committee that the Company&#146;s financial statements were prepared in
accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#147;GAAP&#148;) and the
independent registered public accounting firm has expressed an opinion based on
their audit that the financial statements are in conformance with GAAP in all
material respects. The Audit Committee is not responsible for planning or
conducting audits, or the determination that the Company&#146;s financial statements
are complete and accurate and in accordance with GAAP. That is the
responsibility of management and the independent registered public accounting
firm.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Audit Committee reviewed and
discussed with the independent registered public accounting firm and management
the overall scope and plans for the audit, the quality, adequacy and assessment
of the effectiveness of internal controls over financial reporting, and the
Internal Audit Department&#146;s management, organization, responsibilities, budget
and staffing. The Audit Committee also met with the independent registered
public accounting firm representatives without management present and discussed
the results of their audits, their evaluation of the Company&#146;s internal
controls over financial reporting, disclosure controls and the overall quality
(not just acceptability) of the Company&#146;s accounting policies and financial
reporting.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Audit Committee also
discussed with the representatives of the independent registered public
accounting firm the matters required to be discussed by Statement on Auditing
Standards No.&nbsp;61, <i>Communication with Audit
Committees</i>, as amended, the independent registered public accounting
firm&#146;s independence from the Company and its management, including the matters
in the written disclosures and letter furnished to the Audit Committee by the
independent registered public accounting firm and required by Independence
Standards Board Standard No.&nbsp;1, <i>Independence Discussions
with Audit Committees</i>, and determined that the non-audit services
provided to the Company by the independent registered public accounting firm
are compatible with maintaining the independent registered public accounting
firm&#146;s independence.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In reliance on its review of the
audited financial statements and the discussions referred to above and subject
to the limitations on the role and responsibilities of the Audit Committee
referred to above and in the charter, the Audit Committee recommended to the
Board of Directors that the audited financial statements be included in the
Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K for the year ended May&nbsp;31,
2007, for filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.</font></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">42</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='42',FILE='C:\fc\234113224760_D11265_2368140\19818-1-em.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:32 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
Audit Committee also (i)&nbsp;reviewed and assessed the adequacy of the Audit
Committee Charter and (ii)&nbsp;conducted an Audit Committee self-assessment in
which it concluded that the Committee operates effectively and successfully
carried out all of its Charter responsibilities.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Audit Committee<a name="AuditCommittee_000835"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 20.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">James E. Goodwin, Chairman<br>
James G. Brocksmith,&nbsp;Jr.<br>
Gerald F. Fitzgerald,&nbsp;Jr.<br>
Marc J. Walfish<br>
Ronald B. Woodard</font></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">43</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='43',FILE='C:\fc\234113224760_D11265_2368140\19818-1-em.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:32 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;">IX. PROPOSAL 2<br>
RATIFICATION OF APPOINTMENT OF KPMG LLP AS THE COMPANY&#146;S<br>
INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM<a name="Ix_Proposal2RatificationOfAppoint_000944"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Audit Committee of the
Company&#146;s Board of Directors appointed KPMG LLP (&#147;KPMG&#148;) as the Company&#146;s
independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal year ending May&nbsp;31,
2008 (&#147;Fiscal 2008&#148;), after consideration and determination of KPMG&#146;s
independence in light of all services rendered to the Company and its
performance as the Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm in
prior years. The Board of Directors asks that the stockholders ratify the
appointment of KPMG as the Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting
firm for Fiscal 2008. Representatives of KPMG are expected to be present at the
Annual Meeting, with the opportunity to make a statement if they so desire and
to respond to appropriate questions of stockholders.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Independent Registered
Public Accounting Firm Fees And Services<a name="IndependentRegisteredPublicAccoun_001000"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company&#146;s independent
registered public accounting firm reports to, and is engaged at the direction
of, the Audit Committee.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
following table sets forth the aggregate fees billed by KPMG to the Company for
Fiscal 2007 and Fiscal 2006 for audit, audit related, tax, and other services
provided by the Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm:</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Independent

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="64" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:48.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Audit related fees in FY2006
were for a comfort letter, statutory audits of foreign subsidiaries and
acquisition due diligence assistance; audit related fees in FY2007 were for
acquisition due diligence and statutory audits of foreign subsidiaries.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">Tax fees include federal tax return
reviews.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:5.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:8.0pt;">All other fees in FY2006 include
consultation and assistance regarding government contract accounting.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Audit Committee pre-approval is
required for any audit, audit related, tax or other services to be provided by
the independent registered public accounting firm in excess of $100,000 in the
aggregate, with the Audit Committee Chairman to report any decisions to
pre-approve such services to the full Audit Committee at its next meeting.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Information regarding security
ownership of management and certain beneficial owners is incorporated by
reference to the information contained under the caption &#147;Security Ownership of
Management and Others&#148; in Part&nbsp;III on pages&nbsp;7 and 8 above.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 2.0pt 10.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Vote Required<a name="VoteRequired_001204"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The affirmative vote of a majority of the shares of
Common Stock present in person or by proxy and voting at the Annual Meeting is
required to ratify the appointment of KPMG LLP as the Company&#146;s independent
registered public accounting firm.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">THE BOARD
OF DIRECTORS RECOMMENDS THAT THE STOCKHOLDERS VOTE FOR RATIFICATION OF THE
APPOINTMENT OF KPMG LLP AS THE COMPANY&#146;S INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC
ACCOUNTING FIRM.</font></b></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">44</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='44',FILE='C:\fc\234113224760_D11265_2368140\19818-1-em.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:32 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;">X. OTHER BUSINESS<a name="X_OtherBusiness_001216"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Management knows of no other
matters which are to be brought before the Annual Meeting. However, if any
other matters properly come before the Annual Meeting, the named proxy holders
will vote all proxies in their discretion and best judgment on such other
matters.</font></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">45</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='45',FILE='C:\fc\234113224760_D11265_2368140\19818-1-em.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Aug 22 11:32 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;">XI. STOCKHOLDER PROPOSALS<br>
FOR THE 2008 ANNUAL MEETING<a name="Xi_StockholderProposalsForThe2008_001255"></a></font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Any stockholder who wishes to present a proposal for
consideration at the Annual Meeting of Stockholders to be held in 2008 must
submit such proposal in accordance with the rules&nbsp;promulgated by the
Securities and Exchange Commission. Under the Company&#146;s By-Laws, in order for a
proposal to be eligible for action by the stockholders at and inclusion in the
Company&#146;s Proxy Statement and form of proxy relating to the&#160; 2008 Annual Meeting, the stockholder must
submit such proposal to the Company, in writing, to be received by the
Secretary of the Company, AAR CORP., One AAR Place, 1100 N. Wood Dale Road,
Wood Dale, Illinois 60191, no later than April&nbsp;21, 2008.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A
stockholder proposal submitted outside Rule&nbsp;14a-8 under the Exchange
Act for presentation at the 2008 Annual
Meeting will be considered untimely for purposes of Rules&nbsp;14a-4 and
14a-5 under the Exchange Act if notice of the stockholder proposal is
received by the Company after April&nbsp;16, 2008.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">UPON THE WRITTEN REQUEST OF ANY RECORD HOLDER OR
BENEFICIAL OWNER OF COMMON STOCK OF AAR CORP., THE COMPANY WILL PROVIDE,
WITHOUT CHARGE, A COPY OF ITS ANNUAL REPORT ON FORM&nbsp;l0-K FILED WITH
THE SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION FOR THE FISCAL YEAR ENDED MAY&nbsp;31,
2007. REQUESTS SHOULD BE MADE TO MR. HOWARD A. PULSIFER, SECRETARY, AAR CORP.,
ONE AAR PLACE, 1100 N. WOOD DALE ROAD, WOOD DALE, ILLINOIS 60191, (630) 227-2000.</font></b></p>


 <p style="margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">46</font></p>
